#Text=How did they decide who was going to read the Tyra Mail for the episode ?
#Text=Was it random , planned , or was it really who ' discovered ' the note each morning ?
#Text=It 's definitely whoever discovered the note .
#Text=Contrary to popular belief , the show is n't really scripted , planned , etc.
#Text=Were you forced to fake your excitement over Tyra Mail ?
#Text=We were n't forced to do anything , but I think that we all knew what our " expected " reactions were to the Tyra Mail readings .
#Text=We had all seen the show , we all knew what the girls acted like when Tyra Mail was read , so we basically just kind of did the same thing .
#Text=It 's supposed to be an exciting moment , you know ?
#Text=Whitney takes more fan questions
#Text=Do you still keep in touch with girls from your cycle ?
#Text=If so , who ?
#Text=Most definitely .
#Text=I probably have hung out with Jaslene the most since we both live in New York together and that was my girl from the beginning .
#Text=Diana and I still keep in touch .
#Text=I still speak to Felicia every now and then , and Kathleen and I have been out on the town ( she does n't know it yet , but she 's my new hairdresser too .
#Text=That girl has got a fierce weave game . )
#Text=What were the pressures like in the house ?
#Text=I actually felt like the house was my refuge .
#Text=It was home !

#Text=It was where I could go and let my hair down , go to sleep , read a book , call my friends and family , etc. Some of the girls might say they hated it in the house , but I was really cool with mostly all of the girls so the house was somewhere I knew I could be and just be Whitney .
#Text=Is it common for agencies or clients to contact you after seeing the show ?
#Text=No way .
#Text=Models come a dime a dozen .
#Text=Established modeling agencies have no reason to go out and chase girls .
#Text=I 'd say it 's more common for companies to contact girls about making special appearances , but not modeling agencies .
#Text=It 's up to you to go out and find a modeling agency .
#Text=And do you get contacted from the guest designers that appeared on your cycle ?
#Text=I , personally , never have .
#Text=A fan really wanted to know , " Was Dionne as funny as she was on the show ? "
#Text=Dionne was really quiet and reserved .
#Text=I was actually surprised to see how comedic she came off during her interviews .
#Text=How did you feel when Dionne and Renee only got T-shirts as a prize for winning the acting challenge ?
#Text=Like I was the luckiest person in the world for winning the laser beam challenge . [ laughs ]
